The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification in video setting, which involves learning effective representations from video sequences with heterogeneous spatial-temporal information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for this problem, which involves the use of residual networks and a spatial-temporal smooth module. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which involves searching for a specific person in a large dataset, suggesting that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
